{
  "texts": [
    "At the same time, code generated by LLMs may be incorrect [10] or vulnerable [34].",
    "Thus, we need autonomous processes which allow for code improvements, such as bug fixes and feature additions.In this paper, we suggest a LLM-based solution AutoCodeRover for autonomous code improvement.",
    "The key distinguishing feature of AutoCodeRover is its conscious attempt to inject a software engineering outlook by integrating (a) use of program representations such as ASTs instead of files, (b) iterative code search by exploiting program structure and (c) use of test-based fault localization when tests can be constructed.",
    "AutoCodeRover shows significant efficacy in terms of solving real-life GitHub issues.",
    "AutoCodeRover shows that relying only on the GitHub issue description to guide code search for patches / modifications can be misleading."
  ]
}